snippet.description:
Aquaman has been blinded in a mysterious event. Years have passed and soon he regains his sight. However, damage to his land has been done. Its up to him and Mera to find out what happened. 

Hey guys I would like to make it clear that this trailer is fan made. That means it contains clips from other movies, put together with special effects using Wondershare Filmora video editor and Photopea (Photopea.com) photo editor.

‚ñ∫What is fan made movie trailer?

In a nutshell fan made trailers are created for extreme movie fans. That's why its not for everybody because just like Pro-Wrestling, some hate it some love it. If you are into fan made trailers which means you appreciate bringing new ideas to your favorite movies. But my trailers, are not like any other, one word to describe it, REALISTIC.

Editing Details:

Creating Aquaman 2 was challenging because I was not into this franchsie. But my DC lover side made me appreciate this film more. I watched this film once and I thought it was decent. The fresh clips are not too hard to find since there are plenty of cosplay to chose from. To avoid making this dream trailer feel low budget I chose clips from the Aquaman movie it self. Such as the Atlantic City.

The music was great, despite the lack of humor the soundtrack by THE EQUALIZER 2 trailer #2 was great because it had lots of trailer fling to it. The main actor himself had lots of movies to chose from since this is the first time I made a project about him. Not the first Aquaman project though, I did one back in 2020 for one of the trailer style of the infinity saga.

The line "is only a myth" is great connection to how Aquaman is a mystical character. The film SEE had great lines talking about "gods" that perfectly fits this dream trailer. Speaking of perfectly fits, the clip with Aquaman attacks the bad guy we get a transition to a guy getting attacked in the water.

snippet.title: Torn back to Body Shell - The Transplant begins: Amber 2.0
snippet.description:
Can I revive my full-time home on wheels back from the brink?

In this video I'm attempting to take my 18 year old, semi-auto ex-ambulance turned home on wheels and completely revive it, transplanting everything from a low mileage "other" T1n Sprinter & swapping the transmission over in the process.

The donor van has now been stripped and is gone.
The Engine, gearbox, wiring loom and all other vital parts are all now sat waiting.
The last thing left is to tear my van/home completely apart and start this mammoth task of rebuilding it from the ground up, converting it to manual transmission and fixing the ailments that have plagued this van.

I am not from a mechanical background and this is easily the biggest undertaking of any vehicle I've done, there's going to be a lot of ball's ups, going backwards, fits, blood, tears, and moments of victory.
But I have to make this work. If I don't, well my home can no long move.

snippet.title: Project EGG Show #232 - Amber Vilhauer
snippet.description:
Amber Vilhauer‚Äôs life's purpose is helping others feel seen, heard, loved and valued. Her career‚Äôs purpose is to help impact-driven business owners get their message out to the world in the most efficient and powerful way through digital marketing opportunities.

Before founding NGNG Enterprises with Amber Vilhauer (standing for NoGutsNoGlory) in 2007, Amber was an integral part of a multi-million dollar marketing company named Vector Marketing, while also attending the University of Arizona for Marketing and Graphic Design. As a young 20 year old, not only did Amber achieve the highest sales level in the company of Senior Field Sales Manager, she also moved through the management levels very quickly.

From her promotion of Assistant Manager after 3 short months, Amber went on to become a lead Sales Manager for her local district office. She was pursued to move to Denver for the position of Pilot Sales Manager, helping to run a division of 13 offices in 4 states. Amber trained new managers to open their own district office, was responsible for training and managing more than 30 receptionists in the division, all while continuing to recruit and train thousands of sales reps for the Denver district. Amber assisted in coordinating division-wide conferences throughout the year, regularly speaking in small workshop and 300-person conference settings.

At 25 years old, Amber was ready for her next challenge. She pivoted and organized the production of two powerful conferences designed to teach budding entrepreneurs how to grow their business online. As Amber connected with the speakers, some of the top online marketing experts of all time, her passion to test and refine their strategies was born.

Working one-on-one with her author, speaker and coach clients, Amber and her team have created more than 500 WordPress websites. Amber knows how a website needs to function in order to generate sales, build a fan base and attract long-term clientele. She works with clients to build a strong, branded social media presence, coaches each client on which manageable actions will help them achieve their online goals and then walks them through exactly how to do it.

Watch the full episode here: https://projectegg.co/amber-vilhauer

About The Project EGG Show:
The Project EGG Show is a video talk show that introduces you to entrepreneurs from around the world. It is broadcast from studios in Metairie, Louisiana to online platforms including YouTube, iTunes, Google Play, Spotify and Stitcher, and hosted by Ben Gothard.

Our goal is to give you a fresh, unscripted and unedited look into the lives of real entrepreneurs from around the globe. From billionaires to New York Times best selling authors to Emmy Award winners to Forbes 30 Under 30 recipients to TEDx speakers ‚Äì we present their real stories ‚Äì uncensored and uncut.

Subscribe To The Show: https://projectegg.co/podcast/

snippet.localized.title: Project EGG Show #232 - Amber Vilhauer
snippet.localized.description:
Amber Vilhauer‚Äôs life's purpose is helping others feel seen, heard, loved and valued. Her career‚Äôs purpose is to help impact-driven business owners get their message out to the world in the most efficient and powerful way through digital marketing opportunities.

Before founding NGNG Enterprises with Amber Vilhauer (standing for NoGutsNoGlory) in 2007, Amber was an integral part of a multi-million dollar marketing company named Vector Marketing, while also attending the University of Arizona for Marketing and Graphic Design. As a young 20 year old, not only did Amber achieve the highest sales level in the company of Senior Field Sales Manager, she also moved through the management levels very quickly.

From her promotion of Assistant Manager after 3 short months, Amber went on to become a lead Sales Manager for her local district office. She was pursued to move to Denver for the position of Pilot Sales Manager, helping to run a division of 13 offices in 4 states. Amber trained new managers to open their own district office, was responsible for training and managing more than 30 receptionists in the division, all while continuing to recruit and train thousands of sales reps for the Denver district. Amber assisted in coordinating division-wide conferences throughout the year, regularly speaking in small workshop and 300-person conference settings.

At 25 years old, Amber was ready for her next challenge. She pivoted and organized the production of two powerful conferences designed to teach budding entrepreneurs how to grow their business online. As Amber connected with the speakers, some of the top online marketing experts of all time, her passion to test and refine their strategies was born.

Working one-on-one with her author, speaker and coach clients, Amber and her team have created more than 500 WordPress websites. Amber knows how a website needs to function in order to generate sales, build a fan base and attract long-term clientele. She works with clients to build a strong, branded social media presence, coaches each client on which manageable actions will help them achieve their online goals and then walks them through exactly how to do it.

Watch the full episode here: https://projectegg.co/amber-vilhauer

About The Project EGG Show:
The Project EGG Show is a video talk show that introduces you to entrepreneurs from around the world. It is broadcast from studios in Metairie, Louisiana to online platforms including YouTube, iTunes, Google Play, Spotify and Stitcher, and hosted by Ben Gothard.

Our goal is to give you a fresh, unscripted and unedited look into the lives of real entrepreneurs from around the globe. From billionaires to New York Times best selling authors to Emmy Award winners to Forbes 30 Under 30 recipients to TEDx speakers ‚Äì we present their real stories ‚Äì uncensored and uncut.

Subscribe To The Show: https://projectegg.co/podcast/
